HEADWORD: Dendriform
<hw>Den"dri*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>de`ndron</grk> tree + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <def>Resembling in
structure a tree or shrub; having a branching shape.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> arboreal, arboreous, arborescent, arboresque,
arboriform, dendroid, dendroidal, treelike, tree-shaped.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

